# Clerk Auth & Data Access

All authentication is handled by Clerk. Users must only be able to access their own data.

## Getting the Current User

Always use Clerk's server-side helpers to get the authenticated user:

```typescript
// Server Components / Route Handlers / Server Actions
import { auth } from "@clerk/nextjs/server";

const { userId } = await auth();
if (!userId) {
  // Return 401 or redirect to sign-in
  throw new Error("Unauthorized");
}
```

## Enforcing Ownership in DB Queries

Always scope queries to the authenticated `userId`. Never trust client-supplied IDs.

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — fetches data without checking ownership
const deck = await db.query.decks.findFirst({
  where: eq(decks.id, deckId),
});

// ✅ GOOD — scopes query to the authenticated user
const deck = await db.query.decks.findFirst({
  where: and(eq(decks.id, deckId), eq(decks.userId, userId)),
});
```

## Mutations Must Also Check Ownership

```typescript
// ✅ Always include userId filter on updates and deletes
await db
  .update(decks)
  .set({ name: newName })
  .where(and(eq(decks.id, deckId), eq(decks.userId, userId)));
```

## Schema Convention

Every user-owned table must have a `userId` column:

```typescript
userId: text("user_id").notNull(), // Clerk user ID
```

## Rules

- Never expose another user's data, even partially
- Always validate `userId` before any DB read/write
- Never rely on client-provided `userId` — always derive it from `auth()`
